          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toast the nuts",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Spread the {{pecans}} on a baking tray and toast for 7 to 8 minutes until they smell nutty and are lightly browned. Cool completely, then chop roughly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and 50 g of {{icing-sugar}} (for the dough) together until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{vanilla-extract}}. Add the {{plain-flour}} and {{fine-sea-salt}} and mix until just combined. Fold in the chopped pecans. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll the dough into balls about 3 cm in diameter, roughly a heaped teaspoon each. Arrange on lined baking trays with 3 cm between them. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes until the cookies are set and very pale gold on the base. They should not brown on top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Double roll in icing sugar",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put the 150 g of {{icing-sugar}} for rolling in a shallow bowl. While the cookies are still warm, roll them gently in the icing sugar to coat. They will be fragile, handle carefully. Leave to cool completely on a rack, then roll again in the icing sugar for a thick, white finish.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
